pokedexEntries.gold: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.
pokedexEntries.silver: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.
pokedexEntries.crystal: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it's in the water.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Azumarill's long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air balloons if it spots a drowning Pokémon. The air balloons enable the Pokémon in trouble to breathe.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It lives in water virtually all day long. Its body color and pattern act as camouflage that makes it tough for enemies to spot in water.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: By keeping still and listening intently, it can even tell what is in wild, fast-moving rivers.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It lives in rivers and lakes. In water, its coloring and patterns trick the vision of foes.
pokedexEntries.pearl: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.
pokedexEntries.platinum: It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

pokedexEntries.white: It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air.
pokedexEntries.black2: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.
pokedexEntries.white2: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.
